# AgentFrame Consulting Prep — .gitignore
#
# Purpose: keep COPYRIGHTED case content out of GitHub. The system/shape/structure stays;
# the case bodies (and original PDFs) never get pushed. They DO ship in the zip handed to students.
#
# What stays in GitHub: the tracker (shows how cases work), the README, all skills, scaffolding.
# What's excluded: every case body in library/cases/ except the tracker + README.

# --- Copyrighted case content (NEVER push) ---
# Ignore everything in library/cases/ ...
library/cases/*
# ... but keep the structure-bearing files:
!library/cases/.gitkeep
!library/cases/README.md
!library/cases/case-tracker.md

# Original casebook source files (PDFs, docx, etc.) wherever they land
library/cases/originals/
*.casebook.pdf

# --- Source files with real personal info (never push) ---
_source-do-not-ship/

# --- Secrets (NEVER push) ---
.env

# --- Scratch / stress-test artifacts ---
_stress-test/
# node_modules IS vendored (pure-JS docx-js, no native binaries) so .docx generation works out of the box.

# --- Build / cache cruft ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# --- OS / editor noise ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.obsidian/
